fstests-utils release-on-drain <backend-down-cmd> <out-file>

Read wq-ssh JSONL on stdin, write it through to <out-file>, and fire
"<backend-down-cmd> <worker>" in the background whenever a
worker_stopped event with reason=drained appears.

That's wq-ssh's "this worker has nothing more to do" signal; the
pull-model guarantees the worker is idle at that moment, so it's
safe to destroy its underlying VM/droplet.
